description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Successful candidates will be invited to an Assessment Day on Friday 20th November 2020 . Please note this will be either a morning or afternoon session to be confirmed.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cornwall Community Hospitals offer any registered nurse the opportunity to participate in nurse-led care and make contributions to a variety of care pathways. (e.g. palliative care, medical, surgical and orthopaedic cases).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On Lanyon Ward at Camborne and Redruth hospital we have a lovely 21 bedded stroke rehabilitation ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Patients are received from the acute provider and require the skills and knowledge of a competent practitioner, utilising evidence-based practice. &lt;br /&gt;This role provides any band 5 staff nurse with the opportunity to develop their knowledge and skills along the stroke pathway. We offer a fantastic opportunity working alongside members of the stroke specialist MDT team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We need enthusiastic, highly motivated individuals who are able to work well within a team and on their own initiative.&lt;br /&gt;We want you to join our team and strive to deliver care closer to home, in a patient-centered approach. You must possess excellent communication skills, be a team player and have a genuine interest in a specialist rehabilitation service for stroke patients across Cornwall which includes flexible, cross-boundary working within the wider stroke team.&lt;br /&gt;Cornwall is an excellent place to live with good schools, a relaxed quality of life and excellent sporting opportunities, all set within stunning countryside and surrounded by a beautiful coastline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Part time 24.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Denise Williams Ward Manager 01209 318017&lt;/p&gt;
